# Accessibility baseline

When changing UI copy, assets, or components:

- Ensure meaningful `alt` text for non-decorative images (especially logos and hero/product images).
- If an image is decorative, use an empty alt (`alt=""`) and avoid redundant screen-reader noise.
- Keep CTA/button/link text descriptive; avoid “Click here”.
- Do not remove focus-visible affordances or create keyboard traps.

## Repo references (examples)
- Logo image alt text: `src/components/Nav.jsx`
- Hero imagery: `src/sections/Hero.jsx`
